          <p id="IO-UN.2421.1">The General Postal Union was founded by the Treaty of Bern (1874), beginning operations in July 1875. Three years later its name was changed to the Universal Postal Union (UPU). In 1948 the UPU became a specialized agency of the UN. The UPU promotes the sustainable development of high-quality, universal, efficient and accessible postal services, and provides a forum for co-operation between postal sector stakeholders.</p>
          <!--Single postal territory-->
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.2422" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Members</heading>
               <p id="IO-UN.2423">The UPU has 192 members.</p>
          </int-org-section>
